info.title: Pay Data Input
info.description: Pay data input is a one-time payroll change, such as a charity deduction, for a worker.  The Pay Data Input v1 APIs are used to add, modify, or replace pay data input for a worker, or to view all of the pay data inputs appllied to a worker. API metadata is also available.

PayDataInputs.description: This API is used to input pay data for the purpose of running a payroll

PayDataInput.title: PayDataInput
PayDataInput.description: Data that is input into a payroll run

payeePayInputs.description: The term pay equates to a pay statement or check. If all earnings for all work assignments should be on one check, then one instance of this array is passed; if earnings should be split across multiple checks either based on the type of pay, e.g. bonus, or one check per work assignment, a new instance of this array should be sent for each desired check. Manual and voided checks are not supported in this context.
